<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Female.</emphasis>
Body length 6.0-7.0 mm. Similar to male in habitus and colour pattern and with dimorphic T3, acutely arcuate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Holopyga tyrneri sp. nov., female, paratype (A-C, E, F) and H. similis Mocsary, female from (from Italy) (D) A habitus, dorsal view B head, frontal view C habitus, lateral view D metasoma, postero-lateral view E metasoma, postero-lateral view F metasoma, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.73549.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/608685" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">18E</figureCitation>
). Flagellum I distinctly longer l/w = 3.5 (l/w 2.5 in male); posterior propodeal projections more divergent and acute; metasoma with more scattered, minute punctures.
</paragraph>
