<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="149" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Rosa, Proshchalykin &amp; Halada" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga tyrneri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tyrneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Holopyga tyrneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(masculine noun in genitive) is dedicated to Pavel Tyrner (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Litvínov">Litvinov</normalizedToken>
, Czech Republic), who collected and provided data from Mongolia and for his precious contribution to the knowledge of the European 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chrysididae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="149" type="comparative diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Comparative diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Rosa, Proshchalykin &amp; Halada" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga tyrneri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tyrneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Holopyga tyrneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga similis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Holopyga similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mocsáry">Mocsary</normalizedToken>
, 1889 [= 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. chrysonota" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" rank="species" species="chrysonota">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">H. chrysonota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Laurentius Salvius, Stockholm" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" refId="B19" refString="Linsenmaier, W, 1959. Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 32(1): 232 pp." title="Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 32 (1): 232 pp." year="1959">Linsenmaier (1959)</bibRefCitation>
] for habitus and same colour pattern in both sexes. It can be immediately separated by metasoma with noticeably scattered and shallow punctures (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Holopyga tyrneri sp. nov., female, paratype (A-C, E, F) and H. similis Mocsary, female from (from Italy) (D) A habitus, dorsal view B head, frontal view C habitus, lateral view D metasoma, postero-lateral view E metasoma, postero-lateral view F metasoma, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.73549.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/608685" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">18E</figureCitation>
) compared with 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. similis" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">H. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Holopyga tyrneri sp. nov., female, paratype (A-C, E, F) and H. similis Mocsary, female from (from Italy) (D) A habitus, dorsal view B head, frontal view C habitus, lateral view D metasoma, postero-lateral view E metasoma, postero-lateral view F metasoma, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.73549.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/608685" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">18D</figureCitation>
) and by different genital capsule. The female also resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Forster" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga chrysonota" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysonota">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Holopyga chrysonota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Förster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
, 1853) [= 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. ignicollis" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" rank="species" species="ignicollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">H. ignicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Laurentius Salvius, Stockholm" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" refId="B19" refString="Linsenmaier, W, 1959. Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 32(1): 232 pp." title="Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 32 (1): 232 pp." year="1959">Linsenmaier (1959)</bibRefCitation>
] by colour pattern; however, it can be separated by metasoma with scattered, shallow punctures and by denser punctures on S2 (vs. scattered with only few dots in 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. chrysonota" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" rank="species" species="chrysonota">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">H. chrysonota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Forster" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga chrysonota" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysonota">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Holopyga chrysonota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is differently coloured, with mesosoma green, pronotum and mesoscutum usually lighter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
